Ayala, Cebu Air, Glorious Property: Asia Ex-Japan Stock Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-07-07T21:57:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-07/ayala-cebu-air-glorious-property-asia-ex-japan-stock-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes today in Asian trading, excluding Japan.
Stock symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close, unless noted otherwise.  Advanced Semiconductor Engineering Inc. (2311)  (2311 TT): The
Taiwanese chip packaging and testing company posted a 6.8
percent decline in sales to NT$5.63 billion ($195 million) in
June from a year earlier, a stock-exchange filing showed. The
stock increased 1.7 percent to NT$32.70.  Ayala Land Inc. (ALI)  : Aberdeen Asset Managers Ltd. and
Aberdeen Asset Management Asia Ltd. bought a net 28.3 million
shares of Ayala Land last month, boosting their combined
holdings in the largest Philippine builder, a stock-exchange
filing showed. The stock decreased 2.1 percent to 15.76 pesos.  BHP Billiton Ltd. (BHP)  : The world’s biggest miner said
later yesterday its port and retail operations at Port Hedland
in Western Australia remained suspended after a fatal incident
earlier in the day. BHP is working closely with contractor
companies, police and  emergency services  and the Department of
Mines and Petroleum to investigate the incident and establish
further details, the company said. The stock fell 0.1 percent to
A$44.42.  Cebu Air Inc. (CEB)  : The largest Philippine budget
carrier expects profit will decline this year due to higher  oil
prices , President Lance Gokongwei said. Profit, sales and
passenger traffic in the second quarter were “better” than in
the first three months of the year, Gokongwei said. The stock
decreased 1.4 percent to 87.05 pesos.  Glorious Property Holdings Ltd. (845)  (845 HK): The real-estate
developer’s sales in June rose 125 percent to 2.01 billion yuan
($311 million) from a year earlier, according to an e-mailed
statement. The stock fell 0.4 percent to HK$2.50.  Posco (005490 KS): The world’s third-largest steelmaker
offered to buy the shares it doesn’t already own in Thailand’s
 Thainox Stainless Pcl (INOX)   for 2.20 baht apiece, a
regulatory filing showed.  Posco (005490) , which owns 15 percent of
Thainox, offered to buy a stake held by Thailand’s Mahagitsiri
family and will tender for the remaining shares at the same
price, Thainox said. The family owns about 59 percent of the
company, according to data compiled by Bloomberg. Posco fell 0.3
percent to 464,500 won.  Powerchip Technology Corp. (5346)  (5346 TT): The Taiwanese
chipmaker said its debt ratio was 75 percent as of the end of
June. The stock advanced 6.8 percent to NT$4.22.  Taiwan Land Development Corp. (2841)  (2841 TT): The company plans
to sell 150 million new shares at NT$12.50 each to raise NT$1.88
billion, a stock-exchange filing showed. The proceeds will be
used to develop real-estate projects and for investments, it
said. The stock gained 0.6 percent to NT$15.85.  Vista Land & Lifescapes Inc. (VLL)  : The builder of homes
bought back 200,000 shares in the open market at 3.18 pesos each,
a stock-exchange filing showed. The stock gained 1 percent to
3.18 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
